com.wx.io

Class Accessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.wx.io.Accessor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Closeable, java.io.DataInput, java.io.DataOutput, java.lang.AutoCloseable

    public class Accessor
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.DataOutput, java.io.DataInput, java.io.Closeable
    This class allows to easily perform common IO actions. An accessor object wraps an InputStream and/or an OutputStream and provides many utility functions to read/write different types of data.

    Note: For input/output containing text, prefer the usage of a TextAccessor as it handles better text encodings issues.

      • setIn

        public Accessor setIn(java.io.InputStream source)
        Sets this accessor InputStream. If an InputStream was already assigned to this accessor, an IllegalArgumentException is thrown. To reassign the InputStream, use close() first.

        Note: The InputStream will be wrapped in a BufferedInputStream for better performance.

        Parameters:
        source - Source InputStream
        Returns:
        this (for chained calls)
